  "summary": "Loggerhead XSS via filename",
  "details": "Cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in `templatefunctions.py` in Loggerhead before 1.18.1 allows remote authenticated users to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via a filename, which is not properly handled in a revision view.",
